1
00:00:04,629 --> 00:00:06,423
It is true what they say:

2
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:09,968
Pregnant bellies look like a drum.

3
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:16,850
I'm so pregnant that
my guitar doesn't fit anymore.

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,686
So I'm going to play my songs
on this drum.

5
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:21,771
It sounds really cool!

6
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:25,775
Listen, listen.

7
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:29,362
{y:i}Smelly cat, smelly cat

8
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:34,534
{y:i}What are they feeding you?

9
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,206
That sounds great!

10
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:45,378
I know! And I've only
been playing for an hour.

11
00:00:49,007 --> 00:00:53,428
- What are you doing here?
- I came to ask you a big favor.

12
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:58,183
Don't tell me you want to keep
more stuff in my uterus.

13
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:02,520
Okay. Now, see.

14
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,939
I want to name the girl baby Leslie.

15
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:08,902
And Frank wants to name
one of the boy babies...

16
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:12,364
...Frank Jr., Jr.

17
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:14,240
Wouldn't that be Frank III?

18
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:17,702
Don't get me started.

19
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:20,997
Anyway, since there
are three babies...

20
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:23,667
...and we both got
to put our names in...

21
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:29,255
...we would be truly honored
if you would name the other boy baby.

22
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:31,883
That's so nice!

23
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:34,552
Cougar.

24
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:37,889
Think about it.

25
00:01:39,724 --> 00:01:42,769
The One with Rachel's New Dress

26
00:02:30,025 --> 00:02:31,985
I left a bra drying in there.

27
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:35,488
Will your son think it's yours
and be traumatized?

28
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:40,493
Mommy can have a wife.
Daddy can have a bra.

29
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:42,287
It's time to go.

30
00:02:42,537 --> 00:02:45,123
See, that clock's a little fast.

31
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:47,709
We still have 17 minutes.

32
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:50,754
What can we do in 17 minutes...

33
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:53,089
...twice?

34
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:56,968
Well, that's ambitious.

35
00:02:57,344 --> 00:02:58,678
You can ignore that.

36
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:00,138
That's your son.

37
00:03:00,388 --> 00:03:04,893
Believe me, when he's older,
he'll understand.

38
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:08,646
I'll be right there.

39
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:17,572
This is Carol and Susan.

40
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:20,867
- It's so nice to finally meet you.
- You too.

41
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:25,663
- Susan will be in London next week.
- I've never been there.

42
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:27,791
- I'll show you around.
- Great!

43
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:31,211
Also, I was hoping to catch a show.
Any suggestions?

44
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:33,713
There's tons of terrific stuff.

45
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:37,008
I'll go with you.

46
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:40,095
Look at you two bonding.

47
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:42,764
Making us late for the airport.

48
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:43,807
Are you all right?

49
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:47,394
It's just us getting along
is difficult for him...

50
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:50,313
...because he doesn't like me.

51
00:03:50,563 --> 00:03:52,065
Come on. That's...

52
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:55,068
It's true.

53
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:01,491
Do we have a baby name yet?

54
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,077
No. It's so hard!

55
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:06,579
I went through this book
and found nothing.

56
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:10,291
I want a name that's
really strong and confident.

57
00:04:10,542 --> 00:04:11,334
You know? Like...

58
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:14,087
...Exxon!

59
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:18,550
It certainly worked
for that Valdez kid.

60
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:23,471
You want a strong name?
How about The Hulk?

61
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:29,519
I'm not sure about Hulk,
but I like a name starting with "The".

62
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:31,980
You want a good name,
go with Joey.

63
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:34,190
Joey's your pal, your buddy.

64
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:38,069
Where is everybody?
They're hanging out with Joey!

65
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:42,991
If you're going to name him Joey,
you should name him Chandler.

66
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:46,536
Chandler's funny, sophisticated,
and very lovable...

67
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:49,706
...once you get to know him.

68
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:51,416
Joey's lovable too.

69
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:55,211
But with Joey, if you need him,
he'll be there.

70
00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:59,674
Chandler will be there too.
He might be a little late...

71
00:04:59,924 --> 00:05:02,677
...but he'll be there.
And he'll bring you cold soda...

72
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:06,931
...if what you need him for
is that you're really hot.

73
00:05:07,182 --> 00:05:08,850
What do you say?

74
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:13,521
I like the idea of naming him
after someone I love.

75
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:18,568
Joey and Chandler
are both great names.

76
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:23,948
All right, I don't...

77
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:27,994
Maybe I'll just name him The Hulk.

78
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:33,792
I shouldn't have mentioned it.
I wanted to name my kid that.

79
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:40,423
If you hoped to sleep with Joshua,
which one would you wear?

80
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:45,011
It creeps me out choosing
other people's sex clothes.

81
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:47,931
I'm sorry. I'm just so excited.

82
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:51,101
I've been waiting for months.
I got my hair colored.

83
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:54,896
I got new sheets.
I'm making him a very fancy meal.

84
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,065
What am I making him, by the way?

85
00:05:57,315 --> 00:06:01,569
A frisée salad
with goat cheese and pine nuts...

86
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:05,824
...wild rice, roasted asparagus
and salmon en croute.

87
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:09,285
I thought I was making him
filet mignon.

88
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:13,331
You decided to make salmon
because you had some left over.

89
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:16,710
Then you realized if you bitched,
then you would stop cooking...

90
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:21,840
...and you would have to make your
famous baked potato and Diet Coke.

91
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:25,927
I really get crabby when I cook.

92
00:06:29,848 --> 00:06:31,891
So Emily called last night.

93
00:06:32,142 --> 00:06:36,146
And now you're giving me the message?

94
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:42,777
Turns out that Emily is
just crazy about Susan.

95
00:06:43,028 --> 00:06:45,697
They're going
to the theater together.

96
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:48,199
They're going to dinner.

97
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:51,411
They're going horseback riding!

98
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:55,457
God, Susan is so fun!

99
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:00,253
Look, this is just
a little too familiar.

100
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:03,631
For six months
before Carol and I split up...

101
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:08,011
...all I heard was,
"My friend Susan is so smart."

102
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:13,099
"My friend Susan is so funny.
My friend Susan is so great."

103
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:16,519
You think something could happen
between Emily and Susan?

104
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:21,191
Hey, they're going
to the gym together!

105
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,817
Two women...

106
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:25,612
...stretching!

107
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:30,033
They take a steam, things get playful.
Didn't you see "Personal Best"?

108
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:33,703
No, but I'm gonna!

109
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:37,665
Hi! You're crazy.

110
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,709
Emily is straight.

111
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:44,297
How do you know?
We thought Carol was straight.

112
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:48,927
Yeah, definitely.
I don't like the name Ross.

113
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:54,015
What a weird way to kick me
when I'm down!

114
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:58,186
No, I meant for the baby.

115
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:02,023
What's wrong with Ross?

116
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:07,946
Something like this would never
happen to The Hulk, you know.

117
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:10,073
That's not true.

118
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:16,413
In "The Incredible Hulk", number 72,
Dr. Bruce Banner found...

119
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:17,539
You know...

120
00:08:17,789 --> 00:08:21,876
Never mind.
My girlfriend's a lesbian.

121
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:27,674
I'm definitely going to go
with either Joey or Chandler.

122
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,718
You gotta pick Joey!

123
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:32,679
Name one famous person
named Chandler.

124
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:33,888
Raymond Chandler.

125
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:36,975
Someone you didn't make up.

126
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:40,478
There are no famous Joeys.
Except for...

127
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:43,648
...Joey Buttafucco.

128
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:46,985
Yeah, that guy really hurt us.

129
00:08:47,235 --> 00:08:50,405
How about a compromise then?
What if it's...

130
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:52,657
...Chan-no-ey?

131
00:08:52,907 --> 00:08:56,202
Joey? Think about it.
He'll never be President.

132
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:59,456
There will never be a President Joey.

133
00:08:59,706 --> 00:09:01,750
I didn't want to bring this up.

134
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:06,004
Chandler is the stupidest name
I've heard in my life!

135
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:09,090
It's not a name!
It's barely even a word.

136
00:09:09,341 --> 00:09:12,886
It's like chandelier
but it's not!

137
00:09:14,429 --> 00:09:19,642
It's a stupid, stupid, non-name!

138
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:28,985
You're right.
I have a horrible, horrible name.

139
00:09:30,695 --> 00:09:34,532
I'm sorry, man. I'm sorry.

140
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:38,203
So I guess it's Joey then.

141
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:48,296
This is so nice.
Thank you for doing this.

142
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:52,801
Please! Cooking soothes me.

143
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:57,972
So dig in!

144
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:02,602
It all looks so good.

145
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,230
Oh, my God.

146
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,941
I know.
My God, this rice is so...

147
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:10,610
I am so good!

148
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:13,113
Behind you.

149
00:10:13,363 --> 00:10:18,410
They used to live here,
and sometimes they migrate back over.

150
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:22,372
Is there some way
that they could not be here?

151
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:27,002
Farm birds really
kind of freak me out!

152
00:10:30,005 --> 00:10:32,632
Here we go.

153
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:39,097
There you go!

154
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:50,775
Hey! How'd you do that?

155
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,237
All gone.

156
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:56,156
So, farm birds, huh?

157
00:10:56,406 --> 00:10:59,159
It's my only weird thing, I swear.

158
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:04,789
I would have told you.
I didn't know that they'd be here.

159
00:11:11,004 --> 00:11:13,423
Can I serve you a little...

160
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:14,924
What?

161
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:16,134
Nothing.

162
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:21,014
It's just that I know
that they're still out there.

163
00:11:21,306 --> 00:11:24,309
They're across the hall.
That's two doors away.

164
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:29,939
It'll take them a long time
to peck their way back over here.

165
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:33,735
That's not funny.

166
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:38,907
Would you feel better
if we went someplace else?

167
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:42,994
We could pack this stuff up
and go to your apartment.

168
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:45,330
They're working on it.
It's a mess.

169
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:49,334
I'm staying at my parents' house.
We could go there.

170
00:11:49,584 --> 00:11:52,128
They're out of town.

171
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:55,965
It's a huge place,
and it's got this gorgeous view.

172
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:58,176
It'd be very romantic.

173
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:03,348
- What do you say?
- Yeah, that works.

174
00:12:04,307 --> 00:12:08,144
They can smell the fear.

175
00:12:10,188 --> 00:12:12,273
How's Ben?

176
00:12:12,524 --> 00:12:14,734
I asked if he wanted to eat.
He said no.

177
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:17,320
I asked if he wanted to sleep.
He said no.

178
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:20,365
I asked what he wanted to do.
He said no.

179
00:12:20,615 --> 00:12:23,910
So he's sweeping.

180
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:29,082
Any word from Susan?

181
00:12:29,332 --> 00:12:33,920
She said she's having
so much fun with Emily.

182
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:39,384
By the by, did it
ever occur to you that...

183
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:43,680
...maybe they might be having
a little too much fun?

184
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:45,181
What's too much fun?

185
00:12:45,432 --> 00:12:49,936
The kind of fun you and Susan had
when we were married.

186
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:52,313
Oh, my God!
You are so paranoid.

187
00:12:52,564 --> 00:12:54,024
Am I?

188
00:12:54,274 --> 00:12:56,067
Am I?

189
00:12:56,317 --> 00:13:00,405
Susan is in a loving,
committed relationship.

190
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:03,324
Carol, so were we.

191
00:13:03,575 --> 00:13:06,411
Just imagine for a moment...

192
00:13:06,661 --> 00:13:10,248
...that Susan meets someone,
and they hit it off.

193
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:14,919
They're coming back from the theater,
and they stop at a pub for drinks.

194
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:17,422
They're laughing.

195
00:13:17,672 --> 00:13:20,675
Someone innocently
touches someone else.

196
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:22,302
There's electricity.

197
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:24,387
It's new. It's exciting.

198
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:28,141
Are you saying there isn't
the slightest possibility...

199
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:31,770
...of something happening?

200
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:33,188
- Maybe.
- Oh, my God!

201
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:38,443
I didn't really believe it
until you just said it!

202
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:47,410
None of the other kids believed me,
but I swear that duck pushed me.

203
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:49,621
This place is fabulous!

204
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:52,665
This is the downstairs living room.

205
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,626
There's two living rooms?

206
00:13:54,876 --> 00:13:59,422
Growing up here, this place
must have been a real babe magnet.

207
00:13:59,673 --> 00:14:03,176
It would have been,
but my parents just moved here.

208
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:06,846
You should know this place
is a real babe magnet.

209
00:14:07,097 --> 00:14:10,141
Want to make out?

210
00:14:10,934 --> 00:14:14,896
Why don't I put the food
in the fridge...

211
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:17,565
...and we can eat it later?

212
00:14:17,816 --> 00:14:19,776
That sounds like a plan.

213
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:22,904
Is there a place
that I could go freshen up?

214
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:29,160
Just down the hall
and second door to your left.

215
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,748
- Hi, darling.
- What are you doing here?

216
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:38,878
- We cut the trip short.
- France sucks!

217
00:14:39,129 --> 00:14:42,716
This may be a little weird,
but I've got a date here.

218
00:14:42,966 --> 00:14:43,967
Say no more.

219
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:47,637
We'll grab some food, go upstairs
and be out of your hair.

220
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:50,473
That'd be great.
So you didn't get to Italy?

221
00:14:50,724 --> 00:14:54,352
Yep. Sucks!

222
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:19,252
Hi, you!

223
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:21,212
Oh, my God!

224
00:15:21,463 --> 00:15:26,092
I know. I can do more than cook.

225
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:35,852
I like her. She seems smart.

226
00:15:39,814 --> 00:15:42,233
Rachel, my parents.

227
00:15:42,484 --> 00:15:46,071
So nice to meet you.

228
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:53,620
Joshua, that $500 was for groceries.

229
00:15:53,703 --> 00:15:58,500
What, this? Oh, no.
That's not what it is.

230
00:15:58,750 --> 00:16:01,044
Okay, I work in fashion.

231
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:05,340
And this is a real dress, actually.

232
00:16:05,548 --> 00:16:07,842
They're wearing it in Milan.

233
00:16:08,093 --> 00:16:12,222
Part of my job is to wear the clothes
and see how people respond.

234
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:17,644
Then I report back to my superiors
at Bloomingdale's.

235
00:16:17,644 --> 00:16:20,188
Obviously, in this case...

236
00:16:20,438 --> 00:16:22,982
...I am going to report back:

237
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:26,903
"U.S.A. Not ready."

238
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:29,114
Maybe in L.A.

239
00:16:29,364 --> 00:16:30,365
There you go!

240
00:16:30,615 --> 00:16:32,409
Have you kids eaten yet?

241
00:16:32,659 --> 00:16:37,330
We were going to do that after.
I mean, next.

242
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:41,793
Why don't we all
get something to eat?

243
00:16:43,545 --> 00:16:49,009
No use wasting this baby
just lying around the house.

244
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,011
So we'll go eat.

245
00:16:51,261 --> 00:16:53,138
You'll wear that.

246
00:16:53,388 --> 00:16:58,226
We'll be eating and,
of course, you'll be wearing that.

247
00:16:59,144 --> 00:17:01,312
I am sorry about what I said.

248
00:17:01,563 --> 00:17:05,358
Nope, you're right.
It is a ridiculous name!

249
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:06,401
It's not bad.

250
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:08,737
Yes, it is!

251
00:17:08,987 --> 00:17:13,450
From now on, I have no first name.

252
00:17:13,908 --> 00:17:17,620
You're just Bing?

253
00:17:17,954 --> 00:17:20,415
I have no name.

254
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:23,209
So what are we supposed to call you?

255
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:27,172
Okay, for now, temporarily,
you can call me...

256
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:29,841
...Clint.

257
00:17:30,091 --> 00:17:33,136
No way are you cool enough
to pull off "Clint".

258
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:36,598
What name am I
cool enough to pull off?

259
00:17:36,848 --> 00:17:39,225
Gene.

260
00:17:40,643 --> 00:17:41,644
It's Clint.

261
00:17:41,895 --> 00:17:44,147
It's Clint!

262
00:17:44,397 --> 00:17:47,067
Bye, Gene.

263
00:17:47,525 --> 00:17:50,779
It's Clint!

264
00:17:53,198 --> 00:17:56,618
What's up with Gene?

265
00:17:59,037 --> 00:18:01,373
You wore your nightie to dinner?

266
00:18:01,623 --> 00:18:05,335
The best part was when the waiter
spilled water down my back.

267
00:18:05,585 --> 00:18:09,964
I jumped up and my boob popped out.

268
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:14,135
It's all right.
I got nice boobs.

269
00:18:15,345 --> 00:18:17,639
I just picked up
a message from Emily.

270
00:18:17,889 --> 00:18:20,934
She and Susan are going
to a poetry reading together.

271
00:18:21,184 --> 00:18:23,269
So?

272
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,355
Poetry?

273
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:27,649
Susan's gay.

274
00:18:27,899 --> 00:18:30,985
They're being gay together!

275
00:18:31,236 --> 00:18:32,153
Emily's straight.

276
00:18:32,404 --> 00:18:35,907
Oh, wake up!

277
00:18:37,575 --> 00:18:39,953
Carol really messed you up.

278
00:18:40,203 --> 00:18:41,496
Excuse me?

279
00:18:41,746 --> 00:18:45,750
She turned you into
this untrusting, crazy, jealous...

280
00:18:46,001 --> 00:18:48,586
...sycophant!

281
00:18:50,672 --> 00:18:55,260
So I don't know what "sycophant" means,
but the rest is right.

282
00:18:55,510 --> 00:19:00,598
What are you talking about?
I am not a crazy, jealous person.

283
00:19:02,851 --> 00:19:04,102
She's right.

284
00:19:04,352 --> 00:19:08,231
When we were together, you got upset
about Mark, and there was nothing.

285
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:09,649
This makes sense.

286
00:19:09,899 --> 00:19:11,401
It does not!

287
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:14,237
In high school,
you weren't jealous at all...

288
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:18,992
...even though all your girlfriends
cheated on you.

289
00:19:18,992 --> 00:19:22,203
So up until '92, '93,
he was very trusting.

290
00:19:22,454 --> 00:19:27,334
Then '94 hit, Carol left him,
and bam! Paranoid City!

291
00:19:27,584 --> 00:19:28,918
Absolutely!

292
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:30,837
This is so fun!

293
00:19:31,087 --> 00:19:34,549
This is not fun!

294
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:37,260
All we're trying to say is...

295
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:43,224
...don't let what happened with Carol
ruin what you've got with Emily.

296
00:19:43,475 --> 00:19:47,020
The '92 Ross wouldn't.

297
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:55,236
I still think I was right
about that Mark thing.

298
00:19:55,487 --> 00:20:00,283
Well, you know what?
I hope Emily is a lesbian.

299
00:20:04,412 --> 00:20:07,374
Drumroll.

300
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:10,627
All right.

301
00:20:10,877 --> 00:20:12,003
Help!

302
00:20:12,253 --> 00:20:15,840
Am I a Mark or a John?

303
00:20:16,091 --> 00:20:19,177
You're not tall enough to be a Mark.

304
00:20:19,427 --> 00:20:23,431
But you might make a good Barney.

305
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,974
Look, I am serious.

306
00:20:25,225 --> 00:20:27,477
Tomorrow at 3:30, I'm going
to the courthouse.

307
00:20:27,727 --> 00:20:29,312
You're going through with this?

308
00:20:29,562 --> 00:20:32,065
This name has held me back
my entire life.

309
00:20:32,315 --> 00:20:36,194
It's why kids picked on me
and why I never do well with women.

310
00:20:36,444 --> 00:20:41,741
So tomorrow, I'll either be
Mark Johnson or John Markson.

311
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:46,371
You've got problems because of you,
not your name!

312
00:20:46,996 --> 00:20:50,625
This has got to stop!
Chandler is a great name.

313
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:53,878
In fact...

314
00:20:55,255 --> 00:20:59,134
I'm sorry, I know you wanted me
to name the baby Joey.

315
00:20:59,384 --> 00:21:04,431
I'm going to name the baby Chandler.

316
00:21:06,057 --> 00:21:06,850
Really?

317
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:09,185
But you have to keep the name too.

318
00:21:09,436 --> 00:21:11,563
Okay, thanks!

319
00:21:11,813 --> 00:21:14,941
You want to hug it out?

320
00:21:17,152 --> 00:21:21,656
I'm going to go tell
Frank and Alice right now!

321
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:24,284
Bye, Pheebs!

322
00:21:44,971 --> 00:21:48,808
- Nice luggage.
- I was going to say.

323
00:21:52,896 --> 00:21:54,731
I missed you too.

324
00:21:54,981 --> 00:21:59,986
- Thanks, I had a great time.
- So did I.

325
00:22:00,403 --> 00:22:03,740
No tongue.
